cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SI 

This paper deals with the theoretical study of a hybrid model of differential privacy, which combines local randomizers with a small curator. This topic is closely related to computer security (cs.CR), as it concerns the protection of sensitive data. The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and protocols (cs.DS), as well as the study of statistical learning theory (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the practical applications of differential privacy (cs.SI).
